<dl class="specification-list">

        <dt>Identification and Creation</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
            <dt>Object Number</dt>
            <dd>1937.31</dd>

                            <dt>People</dt>
                <dd>
                                                                 <a href=https://www.harvardartmuseums.org/collections/person/27029>John La Farge</a>, American                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          (New York, NY 1835 - 1910 Providence, RI)
                                            <br>
                                    </dd>
            
                            <dt>Title</dt>
                <dd>Virgil</dd>
            
                                                                                                            
                            <dt>Classification</dt>
                <dd>Paintings</dd>
                                        <dt>Work Type</dt>
                <dd>
                                                            painting                                                      </dd>
                                        <dt>Date</dt>
                <dd>1874</dd>
                                        <dt>Places</dt>
                <dd>
                                                            Creation Place: North America, United States                                                      </dd>
                                                    <dt>Culture</dt>
                <dd>American</dd>
                            <dt>Persistent Link</dt>
                <dd><a href="https://hvrd.art/o/230909">https://hvrd.art/o/230909</a></dd>
          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                <dt>Physical Descriptions</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Oil on linen canvas</dd>
            
           
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>107 x 81.6 cm (42 1/8 x 32 1/8 in.)<br />
framed: 135.9 x 112.4 x 7.6 cm (53 1/2 x 44 1/4 x 3 in.)</dd>
            
            
            
            
            
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>Sale of the artist to Ortgies and Co., New York, 1884; their sale to Thomas Benedict Clarke, New York; his sale through Ortgies and Co., New York, to Robert Hoe, New York, 1886; his sale through the American Art Association, New York, to Knoedler and Co., New York, 1911; their sale to Grace Edith Barnes, New York, 1914; her sale to Mrs. William H. Bliss, New York, 1914; her gift to her son, Robert Woods Bliss, New York, 1936.</dd>
        
        
        
        <dt>Acquisition and Rights</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Credit Line</dt>
              <dd>Harvard Art Museums/Fogg Museum, Gift of The Honorable and Mrs. Robert Woods Bliss</dd>
            
            
                          <dt>Accession Year</dt>
              <dd>1937</dd>
            
            <dt>Object Number</dt>
            <dd>1937.31</dd>

                          <dt>Division</dt>
              <dd>European and American Art</dd>
            
                          <dt>Contact</dt>
              <dd><a href="mailto:am_europeanamerican@harvard.edu"><span>am_europeanamerican@harvard.edu</span></a></dd>
                               		  <dd>The Harvard Art Museums encourage the use of images found on this website for personal, noncommercial use, including educational and scholarly purposes. To request a higher resolution file of this image, please submit an <a href="https://www.harvardartmuseums.org/imagerequest"><span>online request.</span></a></dd>
          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                  <dt>Publication History</dt>
          <dd>
                                        <p>
                               "Art Babble", <em>New York News Letter</em> (New York, NY, April 20, 1884)
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                               "Fine Arts", <em>The New York Herald</em> (New York, NY, April 18, 1884), p. 10
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              <em>The John La Farge Collection, Oil and Water Colors</em>, exh. cat., Ortgies & Co. (New York, 1884), no. 29
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                               <em>Illustrated Catalogue...of Art Property... Collected by the Late Robert Hoe of New York</em>, auct. cat., American Art Galleries (New York, NY, February 15, 1911)
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Josephine L. Allen, "Exhibition of the Work of John La Farge", <em>The Bulletin of the Metropolitan Museum of Art</em>, The Metropolitan Museum of Art (New York, NY, April 1936), vol. XXXI, no. 4, pp. 74-78, p. 77
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Ann Hamilton Sayre, "The Complete Work of John La Farge at the Metropolitan", <em>Art News</em> (March 28, 1936), pp. 5-6, 12, p. 28
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              The Metropolitan Museum of Art, <em>An Exhibition of the Work of John La Farge</em>, exh. cat., Blanchard Press, Inc. (New York, NY, 1936), no. 20, reproduced
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              James L. Yarnall, "Nature and Art in the Painting of John LaFarge", <em>John LaFarge</em>, Abbeville Press (New York, NY, 1987), fig. 67, p. 98, reproduced in b/w
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Theodore E. Stebbins, Jr., Virginia Anderson, and Kimberly Orcutt, ed., <em>American Paintings at Harvard, Volume Two, Paintings, Drawings, Pastels and Stained Glass by Artists Born 1826-1856</em>, Harvard Art Museums and Yale University Press (U.S.) (Cambridge, MA and New Haven, CT, 2008), p. 189, cat. no. 146, reproduced in color
                             </p>
                                    </dd>
        
                  <dt>Exhibition History</dt>
          <dd>
                          <p>
                              <em>[John La Farge exhibition]</em>, Leonard's Gallery, Boston, 01/01/1879 - 12/31/1879
                            </p>
                          <p>
                              <em>Unidentified Exhibition, American Art Galleries, 1883</em>, American Art Galleries, 01/01/1883 - 12/31/1883
                            </p>
                          <p>
                              <em>Hoe Collection</em>, American Art Galleries, 02/16/1918 - 02/17/1918
                            </p>
                          <p>
                              <em>An Exhibition of the Work of John La Farge</em>, The Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, 03/23/1936 - 04/26/1936
                            </p>
                      </dd>
        
        

        
      
      
        
                          <dt> </dt>
          <dd>
                        <p>This record has been reviewed by the curatorial staff but may be incomplete. Our records are frequently revised and enhanced. For more information please contact the Division of European and American Art at <a href="mailto:am_europeanamerican@harvard.edu"><span>am_europeanamerican@harvard.edu</span></a></p>
                        </dd>
                      </dl>
